en_398286_0	Two police officers have been hospitalized following a shooting in Akuressa this morning.
en_398286_1	According to the police, an individual who had been riding pillion on a motorcycle who had ignored the signals to stop, had fired gunshots at the policemen.
en_398286_2	The Police said that the incident had happened in the wee hours of today.
en_398286_3	Two Police officers who were on mobile patrol on a motorbike had observed three persons travelling on a motorbike without a number plate.
en_398286_4	Accordingly they were signaled to halt.
en_398286_5	But ignoring Police orders the motorbike had crossed to the Siyambalagoda road and fled.
en_398286_6	The two Police Officers were injured when the cyclists opened fire at the Police Officers.
en_398286_7	The injured policemen have been admitted to the Akuressa Hospital and thereafter transferred to the Matara Hospital.
en_398286_8	The Police said that operations are underway to apprehend the suspects.
en_398286_9	Meanwhile, one person has died following a shooting that occurred in a bus in Elpitiya this morning.
en_398286_10	Police said the bus had been heading towards Elpitiya from Aluthgama at the time of the incident.
en_398286_11	The victim, 41-year old victim had died upon admission to the Elpitiya hospital.
en_398286_12	Police added that a search operation is underway to locate the suspect who had fled the area after carrying out the shooting.
